script.name: plugin.autotrade.local
script.description: LT UT: Galaxy trading main routine

line.comment: * This script is the Local and Universe Trader, who searches for good trade runs.
* Experience:
* UT: Experience : Jumprange to buy : Jumprange to sell
* LT: Experience : Maximum Jumprange
* Experience General:
* 9 or more: Trader gets a repair at SY when damaged
* 12 or more: Trader needs Jumpdrive and orders it if not installed
* 23 or more: Trader locks stations that he picked as destination
* If Trader does not find any profitable trade runs, ship will wait for a while.
* load experience value
* Set Debug to 0 in production enviroment.
* This will set the homebase of the trader to null if it has less than 50000
* credits available. Otherwise the script will not work as it cannot buy.
* Problem because trader uses money of homebase to trade.
* This behaviour can be wanted so there is a money check.
* enviroment vars
* Variables for trading
* statistic vars
* Start
* Recommendation for shield and fight software settings
* If already docked check if we can use the product
* trade range definitions
* determine free volume of cargo bay
* Find stray wares
* $Wares = array to string: array=$Wares, text separator=',', format wrapper='%s'
* write to player logbook: printf: pageid=8396 textid=52, [THIS], 'I have stray wares in my cargo bay. Please advise: ', $Wares, null, null
* main route selection in getroute
* UTs and long-range-LTs use the stupid routine, short-range-LTs the cool one :-)
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='UNIVERSE trader route long! %s %s buyrange: %s sellrange: %s trade range: %s', [THIS], $start.sector, $buyrange, $sellrange, $traderange
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='local trader route long! %s %s buyrange: %s sellrange: %s trade range: %s', [THIS], $start.sector, $buyrange, $sellrange, $traderange
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='local trader route short! %s %s buyrange: %s sellrange: %s trade range: %s', [THIS], $start.sector, $buyrange, $sellrange, $traderange
* wait if no route found
* No Cargo Space left in ship.
* write to player logbook: printf: pageid=8396 textid=53, [THIS], 'Station locked for sale! : ', $sellstation, $Ware, null
* write to player logbook: printf: pageid=8396 textid=53, [THIS], 'Couldnt find a sell station for : ', $Ware, $sellrange, null
* write to player logbook: printf: fmt='could not sell: ', $Ware, $Value, $Value, $Value, $Value
* Keep emergency jump energy.
* $fuel.tospare = ($fuel.reserve + 3) * $Fuelforonesektor
* skip if $fuel.tospare > $fuel.20percent
* $fuel.tospare = $fuel.20percent
* if $Ware == {Energy Cells}
* $sellamount.new = $sellamount - ($fuel.tospare * $Jumpdrive.installed)
* $sellamount = $sellamount.new
* end
* If currentspace is NOW greater than Scargospace, a stored ware was sold.
* Then the new max space is the currentcargospace.
* Do I happen to be in a trading station
* This is the learning trader system. I use Local Variables as EXP Levels.
* do if $experience >= 18
* $DroneWare = {Fighter Drone MKII}
* Am I able to upgrade my ship?
* Panicroutine Restware an Bord
* If sellamount is 0, the last trade run went wrong. Ignore ware, sell later.
* Litcube edit, Feb 9th 2013
* I keep getting stray wares, so fuck this:
* Exceptions
* v20: Local Trader implemented (Xai Corp)
* v21: major code changes (SymTec, May 2008)
* v23: fixed standby bug (SymTec, Jan 2009)
* v24: outsourced route selection code (SymTec, March 2009)
